{
  "question": [
    {
      "modality": "text",
      "content": "For a rope stretching uniformly from length L at rate v while an ant crawls at speed u relative to the rope, compute the time needed to reach the far end. Output exactly one expression token sequence in plain ASCII only, no Chinese characters, no unit text, no sentence, no equality sign, no chained equalities, and no extra text. Answer format: a single algebraic expression. Use the variable names specified in the problem and ASCII characters only; do not include units, explanatory text, or an equals sign."
    },
    {
      "modality": "image",
      "content": "input.png"
    },
    {
      "modality": "image",
      "content": "input2.png"
    }
  ],
  "solution": {
    "step_1": {
      "modality": "text",
      "content": "Set material coordinate x on the original rope and track the same material point after stretching.",
      "key_point": "Use a mapping from x to x'."
    },
    "step_2": {
      "modality": "image",
      "content": "step2_initial_rope.png",
      "important_bbox": [
        {
          "bbox": [
            0.076685,
            0.342516,
            0.557579,
            0.441317
          ],
          "weight": 1.0
        }
      ]
    },
    "step_3": {
      "modality": "text",
      "content": "At time t, rope length is L+vt, so the mapped coordinate is x' = x*(L+vt)/L.",
      "key_point": "Uniform stretching keeps x/L invariant."
    },
    "step_4": {
      "modality": "image",
      "content": "step4_stretched_mapping.png",
      "important_bbox": [
        {
          "bbox": [
            0.066671,
            0.629155,
            0.780631,
            0.248233
          ],
          "weight": 1.0
        }
      ]
    },
    "step_5": {
      "modality": "text",
      "content": "Relative crawling gives u*dt = ((L+vt)/L)*dx, then integrate x from 0 to L.",
      "key_point": "Reduce to a separable integral in t."
    },
    "step_6": {
      "modality": "image",
      "content": "step6_local_relative_motion.png",
      "important_bbox": [
        {
          "bbox": [
            0.373356,
            0.30982,
            0.283377,
            0.25447
          ],
          "weight": 0.545455
        },
        {
          "bbox": [
            0.375007,
            0.582453,
            0.37493,
            0.281213
          ],
          "weight": 0.454545
        }
      ]
    },
    "step_7": {
      "modality": "text",
      "content": "Solve the integral Lu*dt/(L+vt)=dx and isolate t_c.",
      "key_point": "Logarithm leads to exponential form."
    },
    "step_8": {
      "modality": "image",
      "content": "step8_reach_B_end.png",
      "important_bbox": [
        {
          "bbox": [
            0.255624,
            0.267983,
            0.721907,
            0.372398
          ],
          "weight": 1.0
        }
      ]
    },
    "step_9": {
      "modality": "text",
      "content": "Use the ring-equivalent model: bend the rope into a closed loop with initial radius r_0=L/(2*pi).",
      "key_point": "Translate axial stretching into radial expansion."
    },
    "step_10": {
      "modality": "image",
      "content": "step10_ring_initial.png",
      "important_bbox": [
        {
          "bbox": [
            0.423343,
            0.203784,
            0.18,
            0.09
          ],
          "weight": 0.5
        },
        {
          "bbox": [
            0.464216,
            0.473763,
            0.290714,
            0.121712
          ],
          "weight": 0.5
        }
      ]
    },
    "step_11": {
      "modality": "text",
      "content": "At time t, the loop radius is r=(L+vt)/(2*pi), and crawling remains tangential speed u.",
      "key_point": "Angular increment follows dtheta=u*dt/r."
    },
    "step_12": {
      "modality": "image",
      "content": "step12_ring_expand.png",
      "important_bbox": [
        {
          "bbox": [
            0.42,
            0.18,
            0.18,
            0.09
          ],
          "weight": 0.333333
        },
        {
          "bbox": [
            0.5,
